author: James Whaling
title: Arsenal academy graduate Jack Jebb becomes Sutton's fourth ex-Gunner prior to FA Cup tie
text:
Jebb has signed for Sutton (Photo: GETTY) Share Get Arsenal FC   Thank you for subscribing! Could   
Sutton United have signed Arsenal academy graduate Jack Jebb who becomes their fourth ex-Gunner prior to the FA Cup fifth-round tie between the two sides later this month. 
The 21-year-old has signed for the non-league outfit from Newport, but is still awaiting international clearance from the Welsh FA. 
Midfielder Jebb progressed through the youth ranks at the Emirates but left for Stevenage on a permanent basis in 2015 having had two loan spells at Broadhall Way. 
He joins other ex-Arsenal youngsters Craig Eastmond, Roarie Deacon and Jeffrey Monakana at the National League side. Jebb in action for Arsenal's Under-18s against Chelsea (Photo: Matt Lewis - The FA) Jebb will not feature against his former club (Photo: David Ramos / Getty) 
Sutton host Arsenal a week on Monday at Gander Green Lane having already toppled AFC Wimbledon and Leeds in the competition so far. 
Jebb will not feature against his former club having already played in the FA Cup this season, a 45-minute appearance for Newport in the second round against Plymouth. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
